he error message again: \"SOCKS5 handshake timed out after 10 seconds\" - this is exactly the timeout introduced in `f40fa00`. The handshake is timing out because the proxy server is not responding within 10 seconds.\n\nThe key insight from the user is that \"this only happens when it tries to load the chat, it works fine for the other sections of the app\". This suggests that the proxy works fine for single requests but fails under the polling load.\n\n\nI should check if there's a connection pooling or reuse mechanism that could help reduce the number of handshakes needed during polling.","signature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The problematic change is in commit `f40fa00` (\"Fix network stability and proxy handshake issues\"). It introduced a **hardcoded 10-second timeout** in `Socks5Handshaker.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nusing var cts = CancellationTokenSource.CreateLinkedTokenSource(ct);\ncts.CancelAfter(TimeSpan.FromSeconds(10));  // <-- THIS\nvar token = cts.Token;\n```\n\nBefore this commit, the handshake used the caller's cancellation token directly without an additional timeout. The 10-second limit is too aggressive for polling, which creates rapid successive connections that may queue up on the proxy server.\n\n"},{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_e882c16ee1f14bd18a027225","name":"bash","input":{"command":"git diff f40fa00^..f40fa00 -- Services/PollingService.cs","description":"Show PollingService changes"}}]},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"toolu_e882c16ee1f14bd18a027225","content":"diff --git a/Services/PollingService.cs b/Services/PollingService.cs\nindex 0cf7fcc..a89ded9 100644\n--- a/Services/PollingService.cs\n+++ b/Services/PollingService.cs\n@@ -26,49 +26,61 @@ public class PollingService : ObservableObject, IPollingService, IDisposable\n         StopPolling(sid);\n         var i = iv ?? _def;\n \n-        var p = Observable.Interval(i)\n-            .SelectMany(_ => Observable.FromAsync(async ct =>\n+        var p = Observable.C